main event: A civilian reported seeing one unidentified object near Fairborn, Ohio on October 9, 1968.
interesting points: The witness could not determine any definite movements or other discernible characteristics of the object.
The witness described the object as possibly being a cloud at a higher altitude.
The Air Force requested additional information from the witness to further investigate the sighting, but the address provided by the witness was invalid.
The Air Force concluded there was insufficient data to evaluate the sighting.
